1. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper discusses the process of building event collections by crawling the web, which involves information retrieval techniques such as indexing and ranking. 
2. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) - The paper utilizes the Memento infrastructure to obtain resources from web archives, which is a key aspect of digital libraries. 
3. cs.WEB (Web Technologies) - The paper focuses on web crawling and utilizes web archives, which are both related to web technologies. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper may involve natural language processing techniques to extract relevant content from web pages. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may touch upon security concerns related to web crawling and accessing web archives.
